Name: Eurasian Wigeon
Best seen at: Punjab wetlands, Keoladeo National Park, Chilika Lake
How to identify: Medium-sized duck with chestnut head and neck, grey back, and pink breast (male only)

Name: Indian Spot-billed Duck
Best seen at: Keoladeo National Park, Kaziranga National Park, Sundarbans
How to identify: Medium-sized duck with brown body, green wing patch, and distinctive spotted bill

Name: Mallard
Best seen at: Practically anywhere with water in India!
How to identify: Medium-sized duck with iridescent green head and neck (male only), brown body, orange feet, and distinctive yellow bill with black patch

Name: Northern Pintail
Best seen at: Punjab wetlands, Chilika Lake, Keoladeo National Park
How to identify: Medium-sized duck with long, slender neck and tail, brown body, grey head (male only), and distinctive white stripe on wing

Name: Common Teal
Best seen at: Practically anywhere with water in India!
How to identify: Small duck with green head and neck (male only), brown body, and distinctive green wing patch
